Facts:
That on 12 August 2008, or sometime prior or subsequent thereto, in the Municipality of Hinabangan, Province of Western Samar, Philippines, and within the jurisdiction of this Honorable Court, accused ALEJANDRO NAVUAL ABARRATIGUE (Abarratigue), a high-ranking officer, and RAUL ROBERTO TAPIA (Tapia), Municipal Mayor and Municipal Treasurer, respectively, of the Municipality of Hinabangan, Province of Western Samar, while in the performance of their administrative and/or official functions, conspiring with one another, and with ANALIZA MABONGA BAGRO (Bagro), Administrative Officer II also of the Municipality of Hinabangan, Samar, acting with manifest partiality, evident bad faith, and/or gross inexcusable negligence, did then and there willfully, unlawfully, and criminally cause undue injury to the government in the amount of at least FIVE HUNDRED THOUSAND PESOS (PhP500,000.00), by purchasing Lot 387-E from the heirs of Isidro A. Abarracoso, without the authority from the Sangguniang Bayan of Hinabangan, Samar, their participation being:
(a) Abarratigue signed Disbursement Voucher No. 100-2008081081 approving the payment of PhP500,000.00 to Ofelia S. Abarracoso, widow of Isidro A. Abarracoso, for the purchase of a portion of Lot 387 situated in the Municipality of Hinabangan, Samar;
(b) Abarratigue entered into a contract of sale with Ofelia S. Abarracoso and her children by signing the Extrajudicial Settlement of Estate among the Heirs with Absolute Deed of Sale in behalf of the Municipality of Hinabangan, Samar;
(c) Tapia certified as to the availability of funds in Disbursement Voucher No. 100-2008081081 and signed Check No. 617805; and
(d) Bagro received Check No. 617805 for and in behalf of Ofelia S. Abarracoso.
Upon their arraignment, accused-appellants pleaded not guilty. During pre-trial, the parties stipulated, among others, to the above facts. The Sandiganbayan found that Abarratigue failed to secure prior authorization from the Sangguniang Bayan to purchase the lot, contrary to Section 22(c) and Section 444(b)(1)(vi) of RA 7160 (Local Government Code). Documentary evidence showed there was no specific resolution or ordinance authorizing the contract. Despite this, the transaction for the purchase was completed and the check was issued with Bagro as payee, not the seller. The P500,000.00 was disbursed from municipal funds for the unauthorized transaction, constituting undue injury to the government.
